"Beauty fades, brains stay."
That was our motto.

11:09.600 --> 11:11.467
We came in second in district.
Holla!

11:12.503 --> 11:14.169
Hey, I feel better.
Good talk, Sydney.

11:14.171 --> 11:15.638
Okay, let's get shooting.
Where's the bra?

11:15.640 --> 11:17.106
We don't have it.
We're polishing it.

11:17.108 --> 11:18.107
Really?

11:18.109 --> 11:19.674
Snitches get stitches!

11:19.676 --> 11:21.276
What do you mean,
you don't have it?

11:21.278 --> 11:22.310
Where-Where is it?

11:22.312 --> 11:24.012
Go away!

11:25.081 --> 11:27.082
I think that only works once.

11:27.984 --> 11:29.217
Just throw a shoe at it.

11:29.219 --> 11:30.452
I'm running low on macho.

11:30.454 --> 11:31.921
I don't know what
to say. Who's that?

11:31.923 --> 11:33.122
Timothy is in a panic.

11:33.124 --> 11:35.091
A raccoon ran into the house,
and now it's

11:35.093 --> 11:36.827
in the kitchen stalking
the Italian wedding soup.

11:36.829 --> 11:38.729
Don't let him near that pot.
Raccoons overseason everything.

11:38.731 --> 11:40.363
Okay, listen,
don't let him eat the soup.

11:40.365 --> 11:42.132
But-But shoo him out
with the broom.

11:42.134 --> 11:44.801
I... I don't know where
the broom is. Call Rosa!

11:44.803 --> 11:46.403
You should go.
I can handle this.

11:46.405 --> 11:49.039
No, he's a crisis queen.
There's no raccoon.

11:49.041 --> 11:50.474
No raccoon.

11:51.476 --> 11:52.876
That's a raccoon.
A raccoon.

11:52.878 --> 11:54.111
But, you know, it looks

11:54.113 --> 11:56.013
a lot more mischievous
than cruel, don't you think?

11:56.015 --> 11:57.581
It could be rabid, though.
You should go.

11:57.583 --> 11:59.583
Ah, it's big 'un.
No, no, I cannot leave.

11:59.585 --> 12:02.219
You don't want to leave me alone
with the clients, do you?

12:02.221 --> 12:03.254
You don't trust me.

12:03.256 --> 12:04.923
Of course, I trust you!

12:04.925 --> 12:06.991
How can I trust you?

12:06.993 --> 12:08.927
You're a wild card!
Thank you.

12:08.929 --> 12:10.763
It's not a compliment.
Really?

12:10.765 --> 12:12.798
No.
Oh...

12:12.800 --> 12:15.733
Where is this $10 million bra?

12:16.769 --> 12:19.070
It didn't just get up
and saunter away.

12:23.009 --> 12:24.409
Lauren, stop.

12:25.778 --> 12:27.980
Come to me.

12:33.420 --> 12:34.585
We're dead.

12:35.521 --> 12:37.855
Best Buy, here I come.

12:40.093 --> 12:41.593
"Raccoon nesting
in Gordie's slipper.

12:41.595 --> 12:42.927
Worried he'll never leave."

12:42.929 --> 12:44.696
Timothy's texting you now?

12:44.698 --> 12:45.797
Well, you deserted him.

12:45.799 --> 12:47.132
"Raccoon using spoon
with humanlike hand."

12:47.134 --> 12:48.533
You know what?
I don't like

12:48.535 --> 12:51.269
that you two are talking
behind my back. He's my partner.

12:51.271 --> 12:52.637
Maybe you should be
a better partner to him.

12:52.639 --> 12:54.372
Maybe you should
mind your own business.

12:54.374 --> 12:56.809
"Where is Gordie?" You see,
he's crying out for your help.

12:56.811 --> 12:58.911
You should go home and deal
with this raccoon crisis.

12:58.913 --> 13:00.513
Raccoon?
Oh, they're mean.

13:00.515 --> 13:01.747
Had a cousin once, got bit.

13:01.749 --> 13:03.215
His eyes foamed.

13:03.217 --> 13:05.117
See? Foaming eyes.

13:05.119 --> 13:06.352
Monsieur, you have
received a message.

13:06.354 --> 13:07.887
"Dinner is ruined.

13:07.889 --> 13:11.757
If I am dead when you get here,
know I died defending it."

13:11.759 --> 13:13.892
Uh-oh, sounds like
the missus is angry.

13:13.894 --> 13:15.993
Yeah, you know what?
They should save their drama

13:15.995 --> 13:17.127
for the soaps they watch.

13:17.129 --> 13:18.563
Am I right?
Amen!

13:18.565 --> 13:19.731
You're a monster.

13:19.733 --> 13:21.733
Guys, Gordon and I have
to go use the restroom.

13:21.735 --> 13:22.701
No, I don't.

13:22.703 --> 13:24.636
Yeah, you do.
Yeah, I do. Okay.

13:24.638 --> 13:25.804
Okay, easy.

13:27.373 --> 13:30.008
Boy, the little fellow's
stronger than he looks, huh?

13:30.010 --> 13:31.143
Feisty, isn't he?

13:31.145 --> 13:32.978
You know I don't like
when you snap at me

13:32.980 --> 13:34.346
in front of clients.
Just get in there.

13:34.348 --> 13:35.781
What are you doing?

13:37.083 --> 13:39.518
Do you know why
I'm wearing this tie?

13:39.520 --> 13:40.686
'Cause you don't own a mirror?

13:40.688 --> 13:43.056
25 years ago today,
you bought me this tie.

13:43.058 --> 13:45.725
Oh, yeah. For our first pitch.
Mm-hmm.

13:45.727 --> 13:47.260
The, uh, Progresso
Italian wedding soup.

13:47.262 --> 13:49.195
"I now pronounce you delizioso""

13:49.197 --> 13:51.731
Oh, so that's why Timothy's been
cooking Italian wedding soup.

13:51.733 --> 13:53.733
We were gonna celebrate
tonight with him.

13:53.735 --> 13:54.934
Timothy likes to be included.

13:54.936 --> 13:56.636
So this is why you're
upset with me...

13:56.638 --> 13:58.337
because I forgot our anniversary?
No, I'm upset

13:58.339 --> 14:00.473
because we've changed.
You know, back in the day,

14:00.475 --> 14:02.842
if we didn't like a client,
we didn't take 'em on.

14:02.844 --> 14:03.776
Want to go back in time?

14:03.778 --> 14:04.810
- Mmhmm.
- Step into my time machine.

14:04.812 --> 14:07.280
- Okay.
- We have no clients, right?

14:07.282 --> 14:08.814
We're eating bread sandwiches

14:08.816 --> 14:11.150
because we can't afford
dirt sandwiches.

14:11.152 --> 14:12.886
We're two idiots
with nothing to lose.

14:12.888 --> 14:15.055
But you know
what we weren't? Liars!

14:15.057 --> 14:16.557
We weren't ashamed
of who we were.

14:16.559 --> 14:18.459
I'm not ashamed of who I am.

14:18.461 --> 14:20.161
Really? Tell that
to the old ball and chain.

14:20.163 --> 14:21.996
Or, as you used to call him,
your swimming coach.

14:21.998 --> 14:23.430
Hold on a second.

14:23.432 --> 14:26.065
Speak of the devil.
I guess he's still alive,

14:26.067 --> 14:28.034
unless the raccoon's
pocket-dialing.

14:28.036 --> 14:29.101
Get out!

14:29.103 --> 14:30.636
I want to hear
what he has to say.

14:30.638 --> 14:32.038
No, no, you've lost your chance.
Easy.

14:32.040 --> 14:33.172
Just get the...!
You're hurting me.

14:33.174 --> 14:35.208
There's more where
that came from.

14:35.210 --> 14:36.877
- I can still see you.
- Get out!

14:42.749 --> 14:44.817
And Marvin's guy swears

14:44.819 --> 14:47.286
he can get Lauren out of the
bra as soon as he gets here.

14:47.288 --> 14:49.588
This is a remarkably stupid
predicament.

14:49.590 --> 14:51.890
This is, like,
Brady Bunch level stupid.

14:51.892 --> 14:53.959
As a fan of that show,
I should've known better.

14:53.961 --> 14:55.661
Adriana's leaving.

14:55.663 --> 14:58.530
So... go sit on her!

14:58.532 --> 15:00.799
I don't get paid
to sit on nobody.

15:00.801 --> 15:02.167
Fine.

15:04.470 --> 15:07.038
Adriana, look, you
need to put that...

15:07.040 --> 15:08.406
Whoa. Is that Chanel?

15:08.408 --> 15:09.942
- That is lovely.
- Thank you.

15:09.944 --> 15:12.411
Put that bag back down, please.

15:12.413 --> 15:15.414
Sorry, but you kept me waiting
all day long.

15:20.586 --> 15:23.589
Wait, Adriana, you cannot
get on that elevator!

15:23.591 --> 15:25.591
- We have you for another hour!
- Good-bye.

15:25.593 --> 15:27.126
Didn't you read your contract?

15:27.928 --> 15:29.862
I mean, if you even can read!

15:31.765 --> 15:34.066
What are you saying, tiny lady?

15:34.068 --> 15:36.568
Because I'm a model,
I'm illiterate?

15:36.570 --> 15:38.537
I'm the head
of the Model Book Club.

15:38.539 --> 15:40.005
Model Book Club?

15:41.374 --> 15:42.942
Prove it.

15:45.945 --> 15:49.182
Well, when I think of Kafka's
The Metamorphosis,

15:49.184 --> 15:51.350
two words spring to mind:

15:51.352 --> 15:53.085
"transformative identity."

15:53.087 --> 15:57.556
Yes, the cockroach represents
the ugliness of humanity

15:57.558 --> 16:00.258
surrounded by the
beauty of free will.

16:00.260 --> 16:02.560
Exactly. Sydney,
what do you think

16:02.562 --> 16:05.196
about the final state
of the cockroach?

16:09.067 --> 16:12.737
I'll tell you this much
about the cockroach.

16:12.739 --> 16:14.672
It bugged me. Holla!

16:14.674 --> 16:16.942
But you say you read the book.

16:16.944 --> 16:19.945
I guess I-I missed this one.

16:19.947 --> 16:21.913
I read all of Kafka's
other works.

16:21.915 --> 16:23.281
Name one.

16:24.150 --> 16:25.917
Da Vinci Code?

16:25.919 --> 16:28.453
You're out of Model Book Club!
Damn it!

16:31.758 --> 16:32.990
So, Gordon, where's that

16:32.992 --> 16:34.292
excible little
partner of yours?

16:34.294 --> 16:36.160
Oh, he has some
important business.

16:36.162 --> 16:38.162
Holy cow, high-maintenance,
that one, huh?

16:38.164 --> 16:39.497
It's like having two wives.

16:39.499 --> 16:41.967
Must be everything you can do
to keep him in line, huh?

16:41.969 --> 16:43.602
No, no, not really.
I try not to manage him, so...

16:43.604 --> 16:45.170
Maybe you should start, hmm?

16:45.172 --> 16:46.805
Keep him from wearing
those ugly ties.

16:48.075 --> 16:49.208
Yeah, super ugly!

16:49.210 --> 16:51.543
What-what, he lose
a bet or something?

16:51.545 --> 16:53.478
Hey, you know what?

16:53.480 --> 16:55.581
Just for the record,
I love that tie.

16:55.583 --> 16:56.615
I think it's a great tie.

16:56.617 --> 16:59.151
And I think Simon Roberts
is a great man.

16:59.153 --> 17:00.419
Been on a call. I'm sorry.

17:00.421 --> 17:01.621
No, I'm sorry!

17:01.623 --> 17:02.722
I've been a horrible partner.

17:02.724 --> 17:04.690
I've been ignoring your needs,

17:04.692 --> 17:06.459
and I've been putting
the client before you.

17:06.461 --> 17:08.227
Well, not anymore... because
from this moment on,

17:08.229 --> 17:09.896
I am recommitting myself.

17:09.897 --> 17:11.263
You and I are going to be

17:11.266 --> 17:14.367
partners forever,
the way it used to be.

17:14.368 --> 17:15.635
I want that, too, Gordie!

17:15.637 --> 17:17.636
- He's still on the line.
- Yeah, I got that.

17:17.637 --> 17:18.938
Timothy?

17:18.940 --> 17:20.372
Okay, stop crying.

17:20.374 --> 17:22.773
You know what? You cry.

17:22.776 --> 17:25.010
- Let him cry.
- You be who you are, okay?

17:25.012 --> 17:26.645
You cry all you want.

17:26.646 --> 17:28.548
He loves you, too.

17:29.350 --> 17:30.617
Yeah, I sure will.

17:30.619 --> 17:33.453
This is from Timothy,
you big lug.

17:33.455 --> 17:34.654
Oh...

17:34.656 --> 17:36.856
From me, too.
I love you, big guy.

17:36.858 --> 17:38.091
Love you, too.

17:38.093 --> 17:39.592
Did I just make this weird?

17:39.594 --> 17:41.360
No, I think we were
already there.

17:41.362 --> 17:42.561
Ah. Uh-huh.
Okay.

17:42.563 --> 17:44.630
So, I guess we're
done here, huh?

17:44.632 --> 17:46.932
No! No, no, no, no.

17:46.934 --> 17:49.301
Your personal business
is your personal business.

17:49.303 --> 17:50.602
Yeah, yeah, I mean,
you're going to hell.

17:50.604 --> 17:52.471
Oh, you're definitely
going to hell.

17:52.473 --> 17:53.906
But so's every other
agency we've been to.

17:53.908 --> 17:55.374
Sure.

17:55.376 --> 17:57.809
So, if we gotta pick
the best of the worst...

17:57.811 --> 17:59.945
Might as well be them.

17:59.947 --> 18:02.215
So, you fruitcakes
want to sell some pies?

18:03.551 --> 18:06.620
Why is the pencil wiggling?

18:06.622 --> 18:08.254
That's just an optical illusion.

18:08.256 --> 18:09.488
Not real magic.

18:12.592 --> 18:14.460
It's the end of the road, pal.

18:14.462 --> 18:16.061
I've lost my touch.
I'm no one.

18:16.063 --> 18:17.229
Oh, stop it.

18:17.231 --> 18:19.331
By the morning, the
models will all be gone

18:19.333 --> 18:20.866
and you'll be back
to one-night stands,

18:20.868 --> 18:22.301
making out and
popping off bras.

18:22.303 --> 18:24.270
What did you just say?

18:24.272 --> 18:27.039
Making out and
popping off br...

18:27.908 --> 18:29.742
Why are you looking
at me like that?

18:29.744 --> 18:31.009
Okay, I can do this,

18:31.011 --> 18:32.344
but we have to make out first.

18:32.346 --> 18:33.778
That's how I've always gotten
bras off before.

18:33.780 --> 18:34.846
Yeah, muscle memory.
That's plausible.

18:34.848 --> 18:36.181
Unless you're not cool with it.

18:36.183 --> 18:37.816
Because I know that we're in
a non-hooking-up phase.

18:37.818 --> 18:39.250
Just do it!
Okay.

18:41.487 --> 18:43.154
Oh. Remember the bra.

18:47.359 --> 18:49.527
The models are leaving!

18:49.529 --> 18:51.129
What's taking so long?
In ten...

18:51.131 --> 18:53.097
The bra, the bra!
It's not working!

18:53.099 --> 18:55.199
.nine, eight...
Cool heads, calm hands.

18:55.201 --> 18:56.634
Should I undo the red or the blue first?
...seven...

18:56.636 --> 18:58.403
The red or the blue? The red.
No... six...

18:58.405 --> 18:59.771
five, four...
I'm not sure!

18:59.773 --> 19:01.873
Oh, no! Do the red!
...three...

19:01.875 --> 19:03.508
Just do the red!
...two...

19:03.510 --> 19:05.310
one!
Pop it!

19:06.347 --> 19:08.113
Now, that's magic.

19:08.115 --> 19:10.048
Oh, give that to me!
Ta-da!

19:10.050 --> 19:11.616
Okay, we got it!

19:11.618 --> 19:13.452
Let's do this.

19:13.454 --> 19:15.354
And if I say no?

19:15.356 --> 19:18.124
Then you won't get
to wear this scarf!

19:18.126 --> 19:20.326
Oh, my gosh!
Where do they come from?

19:20.328 --> 19:22.428
I love this trick!

19:22.430 --> 19:23.529
Magic!

19:23.531 --> 19:24.764
All right, ladies.

19:24.766 --> 19:25.998
Look, I may not be

19:26.000 --> 19:30.468
as freakishly tall as you

19:30.470 --> 19:32.003
but I write the checks
around here.

19:32.005 --> 19:33.338
So purses down,

19:33.340 --> 19:35.674
bras out,
and let's shoot this mother.

19:35.676 --> 19:39.244
♪ Your feelings change
like the weather ♪

19:39.246 --> 19:44.216
♪ Went from clear to gray
on that cloudy day ♪

19:44.218 --> 19:47.919
♪ How can I go on
with that bomb in the palm? ♪

19:47.921 --> 19:51.155
♪ Love's so hard to find
when someone's on your mind ♪

19:51.157 --> 19:53.491
♪ Listen, baby... ♪

19:53.493 --> 19:55.793
I see we came
at the right time.

19:55.795 --> 19:57.262
Everything go okay?

19:57.264 --> 19:59.664
Easy. No problems at all.
How was lunch?

19:59.666 --> 20:00.965
Fantastic, smooth sailing.

20:00.967 --> 20:03.868
I'm lying. I briefly lost
the $10 million bra

20:03.870 --> 20:05.604
and the models
made me feel stupid.

20:05.606 --> 20:07.372
It was the worst day of my life.

20:07.374 --> 20:09.374
Well, your father told
the clients to go to hell,

20:09.376 --> 20:11.310
and then he set the lobsters
free in the restaurant.

20:11.312 --> 20:12.677
They made it as far
as the dog park,

20:12.679 --> 20:14.012
and then things got ugly.

20:14.014 --> 20:15.613
Oh, here's an unlikely
turn of events.

20:15.615 --> 20:17.447
Hmm? Timothy wants
to keep the raccoon.

20:17.449 --> 20:18.849
Oh, that's sweet.

20:20.585 --> 20:22.619
How big you think
they make those wings?

20:22.621 --> 20:25.555
Come on. You'd look like
a big, gay hummingbird.

20:26.641 --> 20:31.862
<font color="#40bfff">Sync & corrections by <font color="#FFA500">wilson0804</font></font>
